3. Write a Java program to perform the following operations on a set of students
using arrays:
• Input and Display:
Accept N students’ roll numbers and names. Store them in parallel
arrays. Display the roll numbers and names as entered.
• Remove Duplicates:
Remove any duplicate roll numbers and their corresponding names.
Display the unique list of students.
• Search for a Student:
Prompt the user to enter a roll number to search. If found in the unique
list, print the student’s name and index; otherwise, print -1.
• Display in Reverse Order:
Display the unique students’ roll numbers and names in reverse order.

SOURCE CODE:

package Management;
import java.util.Scanner;
public class StudentManager {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		
		System.out.print("Enter the number of Students: ");
		int n=sc.nextInt();
		int[] Roll=new int[n];
		String  Name[]=new String[n];
		
		//Getting the inputs
		
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
			System.out.print("Enter the Roll No: ");
			Roll[i]=sc.nextInt();
			sc.nextLine();
			System.out.print("Enter the Name: ");
			Name[i]=sc.nextLine();
		}
		
		//Displaying the output
		System.out.println("\n--- Entered Students ---");
		for(int i=0;i<n;i++) {
			System.out.println("Roll No: "+Roll[i]+"-> "+"Name: "+Name[i]);
		}
		System.out.println();
		
		//Removing the duplicates
		
		  int uniqueCount = 0;
	        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
	            boolean duplicate = false;
	            for (int j = 0; j < uniqueCount; j++) {
	                if (Roll[i] == Roll[j]) {
	                    duplicate = true;
	                    break;
	                }
	            }
	            if (!duplicate) {
	                Roll[uniqueCount] = Roll[i];
	                Name[uniqueCount] = Name[i];
	                uniqueCount++;
	            }
	        }
	        
	        //Displaying Unique list of students
	        
	        System.out.println("\n--- Unique Students ---");
	        for(int i=0;i<uniqueCount;i++) {
	        	System.out.println("Roll No: "+Roll[i]+"-> "+"Name: "+Name[i]);
	        }
	        System.out.println();
	        
	        System.out.print("Enter roll no to search: ");
	        int a=sc.nextInt();
	        boolean search=false;
	        for(int i=0;i<uniqueCount;i++) {
	        	if(a==Roll[i]) {
	        		System.out.println(a+ " Found at "+"index "+i);
	        		search=true;
	        		break;
	        	}
	        }
	        if(!search) {
	        	System.out.println(-1);
	        }
	        System.out.println();
	        
	        //Displaying in Reverse order
	        
	        System.out.println("\n--- Students in Reverse Order ---");
	        for(int i=uniqueCount-1;i>=0;i--) {
	        	System.out.println("Roll No: "+Roll[i]+"-> "+"Name: "+Name[i]);
	        }
	        	sc.close();
	}	
}


OUTPUT:

